150 * bad things will happen.

284void Curl_freeset(struct Curl_easy *data)
285{
286 /* Free all dynamic strings stored in the data->set substructure. */
287 enum dupstring i;
288 for(i = (enum dupstring)0; i < STRING_LAST; i++) {
289 Curl_safefree(data->set.str[i]);
290 }
291
292 if(data->change.referer_alloc) {
293 Curl_safefree(data->change.referer);
294 data->change.referer_alloc = FALSE;
295 }
296 data->change.referer = NULL;
297 if(data->change.url_alloc) {
298 Curl_safefree(data->change.url);
299 data->change.url_alloc = FALSE;
300 }
301 data->change.url = NULL;
302}
303
304static CURLcode setstropt(char **charp, const char *s)
305{
306 /* Release the previous storage at `charp' and replace by a dynamic storage
307 copy of `s'. Return CURLE_OK or CURLE_OUT_OF_MEMORY. */
308
309 Curl_safefree(*charp);
310
311 if(s) {
312 char *str = strdup(s);
313
314 if(!str)
315 return CURLE_OUT_OF_MEMORY;
316
317 *charp = str;
318 }
319
320 return CURLE_OK;
321}
322
323static CURLcode setstropt_userpwd(char *option, char **userp, char **passwdp)
324{
325 CURLcode result = CURLE_OK;
326 char *user = NULL;
327 char *passwd = NULL;
328
329 /* Parse the login details if specified. It not then we treat NULL as a hint
330 to clear the existing data */
331 if(option) {
332 result = parse_login_details(option, strlen(option),
333 (userp ? &user : NULL),
334 (passwdp ? &passwd : NULL),
335 NULL);
336 }
337
338 if(!result) {
339 /* Store the username part of option if required */
340 if(userp) {
341 if(!user && option && option[0] == ':') {
342 /* Allocate an empty string instead of returning NULL as user name */
343 user = strdup("");
344 if(!user)
345 result = CURLE_OUT_OF_MEMORY;
346 }
347
348 Curl_safefree(*userp);
349 *userp = user;
350 }
351
352 /* Store the password part of option if required */
353 if(passwdp) {
354 Curl_safefree(*passwdp);
355 *passwdp = passwd;
356 }
357 }
358
359 return result;
360}

362CURLcode Curl_dupset(struct Curl_easy *dst, struct Curl_easy *src)
363{
364 CURLcode result = CURLE_OK;
365 enum dupstring i;
366
367 /* Copy src->set into dst->set first, then deal with the strings
368 afterwards */
369 dst->set = src->set;
370
371 /* clear all string pointers first */
372 memset(dst->set.str, 0, STRING_LAST * sizeof(char *));
373
374 /* duplicate all strings */
375 for(i = (enum dupstring)0; i< STRING_LASTZEROTERMINATED; i++) {
376 result = setstropt(&dst->set.str[i], src->set.str[i]);
377 if(result)
378 return result;
379 }
380
381 /* duplicate memory areas pointed to */
382 i = STRING_COPYPOSTFIELDS;
383 if(src->set.postfieldsize && src->set.str[i]) {
384 /* postfieldsize is curl_off_t, Curl_memdup() takes a size_t ... */
385 dst->set.str[i] = Curl_memdup(src->set.str[i],
386 curlx_sotouz(src->set.postfieldsize));
387 if(!dst->set.str[i])
388 return CURLE_OUT_OF_MEMORY;
389 /* point to the new copy */
390 dst->set.postfields = dst->set.str[i];
391 }
392
393 return CURLE_OK;
394}

396/*
397 * This is the internal function curl_easy_cleanup() calls. This should
398 * cleanup and free all resources associated with this sessionhandle.
399 *
400 * NOTE: if we ever add something that attempts to write to a socket or
401 * similar here, we must ignore SIGPIPE first. It is currently only done
402 * when curl_easy_perform() is invoked.
403 */
404
405CURLcode Curl_close(struct Curl_easy *data)
406{
407 struct Curl_multi *m;
408
409 if(!data)
410 return CURLE_OK;
411
412 Curl_expire_clear(data); /* shut off timers */
413
414 m = data->multi;
415
416 if(m)
417 /* This handle is still part of a multi handle, take care of this first
418 and detach this handle from there. */
419 curl_multi_remove_handle(data->multi, data);
420
421 if(data->multi_easy)
422 /* when curl_easy_perform() is used, it creates its own multi handle to
423 use and this is the one */
424 curl_multi_cleanup(data->multi_easy);
425
426 /* Destroy the timeout list that is held in the easy handle. It is
427 /normally/ done by curl_multi_remove_handle() but this is "just in
428 case" */
429 Curl_llist_destroy(&data->state.timeoutlist, NULL);
430
431 data->magic = 0; /* force a clear AFTER the possibly enforced removal from
432 the multi handle, since that function uses the magic
433 field! */
434
435 if(data->state.rangestringalloc)
436 free(data->state.range);
437
438 /* Free the pathbuffer */
439 Curl_safefree(data->state.pathbuffer);
440 data->state.path = NULL;
441
442 /* freed here just in case DONE wasn't called */
443 Curl_free_request_state(data);
444
445 /* Close down all open SSL info and sessions */
446 Curl_ssl_close_all(data);
447 Curl_safefree(data->state.first_host);
448 Curl_safefree(data->state.scratch);
449 Curl_ssl_free_certinfo(data);
450
451 /* Cleanup possible redirect junk */
452 free(data->req.newurl);
453 data->req.newurl = NULL;
454
455 if(data->change.referer_alloc) {
456 Curl_safefree(data->change.referer);
457 data->change.referer_alloc = FALSE;
458 }
459 data->change.referer = NULL;
460
461 if(data->change.url_alloc) {
462 Curl_safefree(data->change.url);
463 data->change.url_alloc = FALSE;
464 }
465 data->change.url = NULL;
466
467 Curl_safefree(data->state.buffer);
468 Curl_safefree(data->state.headerbuff);
469
470 Curl_flush_cookies(data, 1);
471
472 Curl_digest_cleanup(data);
473
474 Curl_safefree(data->info.contenttype);
475 Curl_safefree(data->info.wouldredirect);
476
477 /* this destroys the channel and we cannot use it anymore after this */
478 Curl_resolver_cleanup(data->state.resolver);
479
480 Curl_http2_cleanup_dependencies(data);
481 Curl_convert_close(data);
482
483 Curl_mime_cleanpart(&data->set.mimepost);
484
485 /* No longer a dirty share, if it exists */
486 if(data->share) {
487 Curl_share_lock(data, CURL_LOCK_DATA_SHARE, CURL_LOCK_ACCESS_SINGLE);
488 data->share->dirty--;
489 Curl_share_unlock(data, CURL_LOCK_DATA_SHARE);
490 }
491
492 if(data->set.wildcardmatch) {
493 /* destruct wildcard structures if it is needed */
494 struct WildcardData *wc = &data->wildcard;
495 Curl_wildcard_dtor(wc);
496 }
497
498 Curl_freeset(data);
499 free(data);
500 return CURLE_OK;
501}

503/*
504 * Initialize the UserDefined fields within a Curl_easy.
505 * This may be safely called on a new or existing Curl_easy.
506 */
507CURLcode Curl_init_userdefined(struct UserDefined *set)
508{
509 CURLcode result = CURLE_OK;
510
511 set->out = stdout; /* default output to stdout */
512 set->in_set = stdin; /* default input from stdin */
513 set->err = stderr; /* default stderr to stderr */
514
515 /* use fwrite as default function to store output */
516 set->fwrite_func = (curl_write_callback)fwrite;
517
518 /* use fread as default function to read input */
519 set->fread_func_set = (curl_read_callback)fread;
520 set->is_fread_set = 0;
521 set->is_fwrite_set = 0;
522
523 set->seek_func = ZERO_NULL;
524 set->seek_client = ZERO_NULL;
525
526 /* conversion callbacks for non-ASCII hosts */
527 set->convfromnetwork = ZERO_NULL;
528 set->convtonetwork = ZERO_NULL;
529 set->convfromutf8 = ZERO_NULL;
530
531 set->filesize = -1; /* we don't know the size */
532 set->postfieldsize = -1; /* unknown size */
533 set->maxredirs = -1; /* allow any amount by default */
534
535 set->httpreq = HTTPREQ_GET; /* Default HTTP request */
536 set->rtspreq = RTSPREQ_OPTIONS; /* Default RTSP request */
537 set->ftp_use_epsv = TRUE; /* FTP defaults to EPSV operations */
538 set->ftp_use_eprt = TRUE; /* FTP defaults to EPRT operations */
539 set->ftp_use_pret = FALSE; /* mainly useful for drftpd servers */
540 set->ftp_filemethod = FTPFILE_MULTICWD;
541
542 set->dns_cache_timeout = 60; /* Timeout every 60 seconds by default */
543
544 /* Set the default size of the SSL session ID cache */
545 set->general_ssl.max_ssl_sessions = 5;
546
547 set->proxyport = 0;
548 set->proxytype = CURLPROXY_HTTP; /* defaults to HTTP proxy */
549 set->httpauth = CURLAUTH_BASIC; /* defaults to basic */
550 set->proxyauth = CURLAUTH_BASIC; /* defaults to basic */
551
552 /* SOCKS5 proxy auth defaults to username/password + GSS-API */
553 set->socks5auth = CURLAUTH_BASIC | CURLAUTH_GSSAPI;
554
555 /* make libcurl quiet by default: */
556 set->hide_progress = TRUE; /* CURLOPT_NOPROGRESS changes these */
557
558 /*
559 * libcurl 7.10 introduced SSL verification *by default*! This needs to be
560 * switched off unless wanted.
561 */
562 set->ssl.primary.verifypeer = TRUE;
563 set->ssl.primary.verifyhost = TRUE;
564#ifdef USE_TLS_SRP
565 set->ssl.authtype = CURL_TLSAUTH_NONE;
566#endif
567 set->ssh_auth_types = CURLSSH_AUTH_DEFAULT; /* defaults to any auth
568 type */
569 set->ssl.primary.sessionid = TRUE; /* session ID caching enabled by
570 default */
571 set->proxy_ssl = set->ssl;
572
573 set->new_file_perms = 0644; /* Default permissions */
574 set->new_directory_perms = 0755; /* Default permissions */
575
576 /* for the *protocols fields we don't use the CURLPROTO_ALL convenience
577 define since we internally only use the lower 16 bits for the passed
578 in bitmask to not conflict with the private bits */
579 set->allowed_protocols = CURLPROTO_ALL;
580 set->redir_protocols = CURLPROTO_ALL & /* All except FILE, SCP and SMB */
581 ~(CURLPROTO_FILE | CURLPROTO_SCP | CURLPROTO_SMB |
582 CURLPROTO_SMBS);
583
584#if defined(HAVE_GSSAPI) || defined(USE_WINDOWS_SSPI)
585 /*
586 * disallow unprotected protection negotiation NEC reference implementation
587 * seem not to follow rfc1961 section 4.3/4.4
588 */
589 set->socks5_gssapi_nec = FALSE;
590#endif
591
592 /* This is our preferred CA cert bundle/path since install time */
593#if defined(CURL_CA_BUNDLE)
594 result = setstropt(&set->str[STRING_SSL_CAFILE_ORIG], CURL_CA_BUNDLE);
595 if(result)
596 return result;
597
598 result = setstropt(&set->str[STRING_SSL_CAFILE_PROXY], CURL_CA_BUNDLE);
599 if(result)
600 return result;
601#endif
602#if defined(CURL_CA_PATH)
603 result = setstropt(&set->str[STRING_SSL_CAPATH_ORIG], CURL_CA_PATH);
604 if(result)
605 return result;
606
607 result = setstropt(&set->str[STRING_SSL_CAPATH_PROXY], CURL_CA_PATH);
608 if(result)
609 return result;
610#endif
611
612 set->wildcardmatch = FALSE;
613 set->chunk_bgn = ZERO_NULL;
614 set->chunk_end = ZERO_NULL;
615
616 /* tcp keepalives are disabled by default, but provide reasonable values for
617 * the interval and idle times.
618 */
619 set->tcp_keepalive = FALSE;
620 set->tcp_keepintvl = 60;
621 set->tcp_keepidle = 60;
622 set->tcp_fastopen = FALSE;
623 set->tcp_nodelay = TRUE;
624
625 set->ssl_enable_npn = TRUE;
626 set->ssl_enable_alpn = TRUE;
627
628 set->expect_100_timeout = 1000L; /* Wait for a second by default. */
629 set->sep_headers = TRUE; /* separated header lists by default */
630 set->buffer_size = READBUFFER_SIZE;
631
632 Curl_http2_init_userset(set);
633 return result;
634}
635
636/**
637 * Curl_open()
638 *
639 * @param curl is a pointer to a sessionhandle pointer that gets set by this
640 * function.
641 * @return CURLcode
642 */
643
644CURLcode Curl_open(struct Curl_easy **curl)
645{
646 CURLcode result;
647 struct Curl_easy *data;
648
649 /* Very simple start-up: alloc the struct, init it with zeroes and return */
650 data = calloc(1, sizeof(struct Curl_easy));
651 if(!data) {
652 /* this is a very serious error */
653 DEBUGF(fprintf(stderr, "Error: calloc of Curl_easy failed\n"));
654 return CURLE_OUT_OF_MEMORY;
655 }
656
657 data->magic = CURLEASY_MAGIC_NUMBER;
658
659 result = Curl_resolver_init(&data->state.resolver);
660 if(result) {
661 DEBUGF(fprintf(stderr, "Error: resolver_init failed\n"));
662 free(data);
663 return result;
664 }
665
666 /* We do some initial setup here, all those fields that can't be just 0 */
667
668 data->state.buffer = malloc(READBUFFER_SIZE + 1);
669 if(!data->state.buffer) {
670 DEBUGF(fprintf(stderr, "Error: malloc of buffer failed\n"));
671 result = CURLE_OUT_OF_MEMORY;
672 }
673
674 Curl_mime_initpart(&data->set.mimepost, data);
675
676 data->state.headerbuff = malloc(HEADERSIZE);
677 if(!data->state.headerbuff) {
678 DEBUGF(fprintf(stderr, "Error: malloc of headerbuff failed\n"));
679 result = CURLE_OUT_OF_MEMORY;
680 }
681 else {
682 result = Curl_init_userdefined(&data->set);
683
684 data->state.headersize = HEADERSIZE;
685
686 Curl_convert_init(data);
687
688 Curl_initinfo(data);
689
690 /* most recent connection is not yet defined */
691 data->state.lastconnect = NULL;
692
693 data->progress.flags |= PGRS_HIDE;
694 data->state.current_speed = -1; /* init to negative == impossible */
695 data->set.fnmatch = ZERO_NULL;
696 data->set.maxconnects = DEFAULT_CONNCACHE_SIZE; /* for easy handles */
697
698 Curl_http2_init_state(&data->state);
699 }
700
701 if(result) {
702 Curl_resolver_cleanup(data->state.resolver);
703 free(data->state.buffer);
704 free(data->state.headerbuff);
705 Curl_freeset(data);
706 free(data);
707 data = NULL;
708 }
709 else
710 *curl = data;
711
712 return result;
713}

715#define C_SSLVERSION_VALUE(x) (x & 0xffff)
716#define C_SSLVERSION_MAX_VALUE(x) (x & 0xffff0000)
717
718CURLcode Curl_setopt(struct Curl_easy *data, CURLoption option,
719 va_list param)
720{
721 char *argptr;
722 CURLcode result = CURLE_OK;
723 long arg;
724#ifndef CURL_DISABLE_HTTP
725 curl_off_t bigsize;
726#endif
727
728 switch(option) {
729 case CURLOPT_DNS_CACHE_TIMEOUT:
730 data->set.dns_cache_timeout = va_arg(param, long);
731 break;
732 case CURLOPT_DNS_USE_GLOBAL_CACHE:
733 /* remember we want this enabled */
734 arg = va_arg(param, long);
735 data->set.global_dns_cache = (0 != arg) ? TRUE : FALSE;
736 break;
737 case CURLOPT_SSL_CIPHER_LIST:
738 /* set a list of cipher we want to use in the SSL connection */
739 result = setstropt(&data->set.str[STRING_SSL_CIPHER_LIST_ORIG],
740 va_arg(param, char *));
741 break;
742 case CURLOPT_PROXY_SSL_CIPHER_LIST:
743 /* set a list of cipher we want to use in the SSL connection for proxy */
744 result = setstropt(&data->set.str[STRING_SSL_CIPHER_LIST_PROXY],
745 va_arg(param, char *));
746 break;
747
748 case CURLOPT_RANDOM_FILE:
749 /*

1092 memcpy(p, argptr, (size_t)data->set.postfieldsize);

1095 }

1385 case CURLOPT_HTTPAUTH:
1386 /*
1387 * Set HTTP Authentication type BITMASK.
1388 */
1389 {
1390 int bitcheck;
1391 bool authbits;
1392 unsigned long auth = va_arg(param, unsigned long);
1393
1394 if(auth == CURLAUTH_NONE) {
1395 data->set.httpauth = auth;
1396 break;
1397 }
1398
1399 /* the DIGEST_IE bit is only used to set a special marker, for all the
1400 rest we need to handle it as normal DIGEST */
1401 data->state.authhost.iestyle = (auth & CURLAUTH_DIGEST_IE) ? TRUE : FALSE;
1402
1403 if(auth & CURLAUTH_DIGEST_IE) {
1404 auth |= CURLAUTH_DIGEST; /* set standard digest bit */
1405 auth &= ~CURLAUTH_DIGEST_IE; /* unset ie digest bit */
1406 }
1407
1408 /* switch off bits we can't support */
1409#ifndef USE_NTLM
1410 auth &= ~CURLAUTH_NTLM; /* no NTLM support */
1411 auth &= ~CURLAUTH_NTLM_WB; /* no NTLM_WB support */
1412#elif !defined(NTLM_WB_ENABLED)
1413 auth &= ~CURLAUTH_NTLM_WB; /* no NTLM_WB support */
1414#endif
1415#ifndef USE_SPNEGO
1416 auth &= ~CURLAUTH_NEGOTIATE; /* no Negotiate (SPNEGO) auth without
1417 GSS-API or SSPI */
1418#endif
1419
1420 /* check if any auth bit lower than CURLAUTH_ONLY is still set */
1421 bitcheck = 0;
1422 authbits = FALSE;
1423 while(bitcheck < 31) {
1424 if(auth & (1UL << bitcheck++)) {
1425 authbits = TRUE;
1426 break;
1427 }
1428 }
1429 if(!authbits)
1430 return CURLE_NOT_BUILT_IN; /* no supported types left! */
1431
1432 data->set.httpauth = auth;
1433 }
1434 break;

1465 case CURLOPT_PROXYAUTH:
1466 /*
1467 * Set HTTP Authentication type BITMASK.
1468 */
1469 {
1470 int bitcheck;
1471 bool authbits;
1472 unsigned long auth = va_arg(param, unsigned long);
1473
1474 if(auth == CURLAUTH_NONE) {
1475 data->set.proxyauth = auth;
1476 break;
1477 }
1478
1479 /* the DIGEST_IE bit is only used to set a special marker, for all the
1480 rest we need to handle it as normal DIGEST */
1481 data->state.authproxy.iestyle = (auth & CURLAUTH_DIGEST_IE) ? TRUE : FALSE;
1482
1483 if(auth & CURLAUTH_DIGEST_IE) {
1484 auth |= CURLAUTH_DIGEST; /* set standard digest bit */
1485 auth &= ~CURLAUTH_DIGEST_IE; /* unset ie digest bit */
1486 }
1487 /* switch off bits we can't support */
1488#ifndef USE_NTLM
1489 auth &= ~CURLAUTH_NTLM; /* no NTLM support */
1490 auth &= ~CURLAUTH_NTLM_WB; /* no NTLM_WB support */
1491#elif !defined(NTLM_WB_ENABLED)
1492 auth &= ~CURLAUTH_NTLM_WB; /* no NTLM_WB support */
1493#endif
1494#ifndef USE_SPNEGO
1495 auth &= ~CURLAUTH_NEGOTIATE; /* no Negotiate (SPNEGO) auth without
1496 GSS-API or SSPI */
1497#endif
1498
1499 /* check if any auth bit lower than CURLAUTH_ONLY is still set */
1500 bitcheck = 0;
1501 authbits = FALSE;
1502 while(bitcheck < 31) {
1503 if(auth & (1UL << bitcheck++)) {
1504 authbits = TRUE;
1505 break;
1506 }
1507 }
1508 if(!authbits)
1509 return CURLE_NOT_BUILT_IN; /* no supported types left! */
1510
1511 data->set.proxyauth = auth;
1512 }
1513 break;

1518 *
1519 * If the proxy is set to "" (and CURLOPT_SOCKS_PROXY is set to "" or NULL)
1520 * we explicitly say that we don't want to use a proxy
1521 * (even though there might be environment variables saying so).
1522 *
1523 * Setting it to NULL, means no proxy but allows the environment variables
1524 * to decide for us (if CURLOPT_SOCKS_PROXY setting it to NULL).
1525 */

1527 va_arg(param, char *));

3015static void conn_free(struct connectdata *conn)
3016{
3017 if(!conn)
3018 return;
3019
3020 /* possible left-overs from the async name resolvers */
3021 Curl_resolver_cancel(conn);
3022
3023 /* close the SSL stuff before we close any sockets since they will/may
3024 write to the sockets */
3025 Curl_ssl_close(conn, FIRSTSOCKET);
3026 Curl_ssl_close(conn, SECONDARYSOCKET);
3027
3028 /* close possibly still open sockets */
3029 if(CURL_SOCKET_BAD != conn->sock[SECONDARYSOCKET])
3030 Curl_closesocket(conn, conn->sock[SECONDARYSOCKET]);
3031 if(CURL_SOCKET_BAD != conn->sock[FIRSTSOCKET])
3032 Curl_closesocket(conn, conn->sock[FIRSTSOCKET]);
3033 if(CURL_SOCKET_BAD != conn->tempsock[0])
3034 Curl_closesocket(conn, conn->tempsock[0]);
3035 if(CURL_SOCKET_BAD != conn->tempsock[1])
3036 Curl_closesocket(conn, conn->tempsock[1]);
3037
3038#if !defined(CURL_DISABLE_HTTP) && defined(USE_NTLM) && \
3039 defined(NTLM_WB_ENABLED)
3040 Curl_ntlm_wb_cleanup(conn);
3041#endif
3042
3043 Curl_safefree(conn->user);
3044 Curl_safefree(conn->passwd);
3045 Curl_safefree(conn->oauth_bearer);
3046 Curl_safefree(conn->options);
3047 Curl_safefree(conn->http_proxy.user);
3048 Curl_safefree(conn->socks_proxy.user);
3049 Curl_safefree(conn->http_proxy.passwd);
3050 Curl_safefree(conn->socks_proxy.passwd);
3051 Curl_safefree(conn->allocptr.proxyuserpwd);
3052 Curl_safefree(conn->allocptr.uagent);
3053 Curl_safefree(conn->allocptr.userpwd);
3054 Curl_safefree(conn->allocptr.accept_encoding);
3055 Curl_safefree(conn->allocptr.te);
3056 Curl_safefree(conn->allocptr.rangeline);
3057 Curl_safefree(conn->allocptr.ref);
3058 Curl_safefree(conn->allocptr.host);
3059 Curl_safefree(conn->allocptr.cookiehost);
3060 Curl_safefree(conn->allocptr.rtsp_transport);
3061 Curl_safefree(conn->trailer);
3062 Curl_safefree(conn->host.rawalloc); /* host name buffer */
3063 Curl_safefree(conn->conn_to_host.rawalloc); /* host name buffer */
3064 Curl_safefree(conn->secondaryhostname);
3065 Curl_safefree(conn->http_proxy.host.rawalloc); /* http proxy name buffer */
3066 Curl_safefree(conn->socks_proxy.host.rawalloc); /* socks proxy name buffer */
3067 Curl_safefree(conn->master_buffer);
3068 Curl_safefree(conn->connect_state);
3069
3070 conn_reset_all_postponed_data(conn);
3071
3072 Curl_llist_destroy(&conn->send_pipe, NULL);
3073 Curl_llist_destroy(&conn->recv_pipe, NULL);
3074
3075 Curl_safefree(conn->localdev);
3076 Curl_free_primary_ssl_config(&conn->ssl_config);
3077 Curl_free_primary_ssl_config(&conn->proxy_ssl_config);
3078
3079#ifdef USE_UNIX_SOCKETS
3080 Curl_safefree(conn->unix_domain_socket);
3081#endif
3082
3083 free(conn); /* free all the connection oriented data */
3084}

3086/*
3087 * Disconnects the given connection. Note the connection may not be the
3088 * primary connection, like when freeing room in the connection cache or
3089 * killing of a dead old connection.
3090 *
3091 * This function MUST NOT reset state in the Curl_easy struct if that
3092 * isn't strictly bound to the life-time of *this* particular connection.
3093 *
3094 */
3095
3096CURLcode Curl_disconnect(struct connectdata *conn, bool dead_connection)
3097{
3098 struct Curl_easy *data;
3099 if(!conn)
3100 return CURLE_OK; /* this is closed and fine already */
3101 data = conn->data;
3102
3103 if(!data) {
3104 DEBUGF(fprintf(stderr, "DISCONNECT without easy handle, ignoring\n"));
3105 return CURLE_OK;
3106 }
3107
3108 /*
3109 * If this connection isn't marked to force-close, leave it open if there
3110 * are other users of it
3111 */
3112 if(!conn->bits.close &&
3113 (conn->send_pipe.size + conn->recv_pipe.size)) {
3114 DEBUGF(infof(data, "Curl_disconnect, usecounter: %d\n",
3115 conn->send_pipe.size + conn->recv_pipe.size));
3116 return CURLE_OK;
3117 }
3118
3119 if(conn->dns_entry != NULL) {
3120 Curl_resolv_unlock(data, conn->dns_entry);
3121 conn->dns_entry = NULL;
3122 }
3123
3124 Curl_hostcache_prune(data); /* kill old DNS cache entries */
3125
3126#if !defined(CURL_DISABLE_HTTP) && defined(USE_NTLM)
3127 /* Cleanup NTLM connection-related data */
3128 Curl_http_ntlm_cleanup(conn);
3129#endif
3130
3131 if(conn->handler->disconnect)
3132 /* This is set if protocol-specific cleanups should be made */
3133 conn->handler->disconnect(conn, dead_connection);
3134
3135 /* unlink ourselves! */
3136 infof(data, "Closing connection %ld\n", conn->connection_id);
3137 Curl_conncache_remove_conn(data->state.conn_cache, conn);
3138
3139 free_fixed_hostname(&conn->host);
3140 free_fixed_hostname(&conn->conn_to_host);
3141 free_fixed_hostname(&conn->http_proxy.host);
3142 free_fixed_hostname(&conn->socks_proxy.host);
3143
3144 Curl_ssl_close(conn, FIRSTSOCKET);
3145
3146 /* Indicate to all handles on the pipe that we're dead */
3147 if(Curl_pipeline_wanted(data->multi, CURLPIPE_ANY)) {
3148 signalPipeClose(&conn->send_pipe, TRUE);
3149 signalPipeClose(&conn->recv_pipe, TRUE);
3150 }
3151
3152 conn_free(conn);
3153
3154 return CURLE_OK;
3155}

3157/*
3158 * This function should return TRUE if the socket is to be assumed to
3159 * be dead. Most commonly this happens when the server has closed the
3160 * connection due to inactivity.
3161 */
3162static bool SocketIsDead(curl_socket_t sock)
3163{
3164 int sval;
3165 bool ret_val = TRUE;
3166
3167 sval = SOCKET_READABLE(sock, 0);
3168 if(sval == 0)
3169 /* timeout */
3170 ret_val = FALSE;
3171
3172 return ret_val;
3173}

3175/*
3176 * IsPipeliningPossible()
3177 *
3178 * Return a bitmask with the available pipelining and multiplexing options for
3179 * the given requested connection.
3180 */
3181static int IsPipeliningPossible(const struct Curl_easy *handle,
3182 const struct connectdata *conn)
3183{
3184 int avail = 0;
3185
3186 /* If a HTTP protocol and pipelining is enabled */
3187 if((conn->handler->protocol & PROTO_FAMILY_HTTP) &&
3188 (!conn->bits.protoconnstart || !conn->bits.close)) {
3189
3190 if(Curl_pipeline_wanted(handle->multi, CURLPIPE_HTTP1) &&
3191 (handle->set.httpversion != CURL_HTTP_VERSION_1_0) &&
3192 (handle->set.httpreq == HTTPREQ_GET ||
3193 handle->set.httpreq == HTTPREQ_HEAD))
3194 /* didn't ask for HTTP/1.0 and a GET or HEAD */
3195 avail |= CURLPIPE_HTTP1;
3196
3197 if(Curl_pipeline_wanted(handle->multi, CURLPIPE_MULTIPLEX) &&
3198 (handle->set.httpversion >= CURL_HTTP_VERSION_2))
3199 /* allows HTTP/2 */
3200 avail |= CURLPIPE_MULTIPLEX;
3201 }
3202 return avail;
3203}

3205int Curl_removeHandleFromPipeline(struct Curl_easy *handle,
3206 struct curl_llist *pipeline)
3207{
3208 if(pipeline) {
3209 struct curl_llist_element *curr;
3210
3211 curr = pipeline->head;
3212 while(curr) {
3213 if(curr->ptr == handle) {
3214 Curl_llist_remove(pipeline, curr, NULL);
3215 return 1; /* we removed a handle */
3216 }
3217 curr = curr->next;
3218 }
3219 }
3220
3221 return 0;
3222}

3248/* remove the specified connection from all (possible) pipelines and related
3249 queues */
3250void Curl_getoff_all_pipelines(struct Curl_easy *data,
3251 struct connectdata *conn)
3252{
3253 bool recv_head = (conn->readchannel_inuse &&
3254 Curl_recvpipe_head(data, conn));
3255 bool send_head = (conn->writechannel_inuse &&
3256 Curl_sendpipe_head(data, conn));
3257
3258 if(Curl_removeHandleFromPipeline(data, &conn->recv_pipe) && recv_head)
3259 Curl_pipeline_leave_read(conn);
3260 if(Curl_removeHandleFromPipeline(data, &conn->send_pipe) && send_head)
3261 Curl_pipeline_leave_write(conn);
3262}

3264static void signalPipeClose(struct curl_llist *pipeline, bool pipe_broke)
3265{
3266 struct curl_llist_element *curr;
3267
3268 if(!pipeline)
3269 return;
3270
3271 curr = pipeline->head;
3272 while(curr) {
3273 struct curl_llist_element *next = curr->next;
3274 struct Curl_easy *data = (struct Curl_easy *) curr->ptr;
3275
3276#ifdef DEBUGBUILD /* debug-only code */
3277 if(data->magic != CURLEASY_MAGIC_NUMBER) {
3278 /* MAJOR BADNESS */
3279 infof(data, "signalPipeClose() found BAAD easy handle\n");
3280 }
3281#endif
3282
3283 if(pipe_broke)
3284 data->state.pipe_broke = TRUE;
3285 Curl_multi_handlePipeBreak(data);
3286 Curl_llist_remove(pipeline, curr, NULL);
3287 curr = next;
3288 }
3289}

3291/*
3292 * This function finds the connection in the connection
3293 * cache that has been unused for the longest time.
3294 *
3295 * Returns the pointer to the oldest idle connection, or NULL if none was
3296 * found.
3297 */
3298struct connectdata *
3299Curl_oldest_idle_connection(struct Curl_easy *data)
3300{
3301 struct conncache *bc = data->state.conn_cache;
3302 struct curl_hash_iterator iter;
3303 struct curl_llist_element *curr;
3304 struct curl_hash_element *he;
3305 time_t highscore =- 1;
3306 time_t score;
3307 struct curltime now;
3308 struct connectdata *conn_candidate = NULL;
3309 struct connectbundle *bundle;
3310
3311 now = Curl_tvnow();
3312
3313 Curl_hash_start_iterate(&bc->hash, &iter);
3314
3315 he = Curl_hash_next_element(&iter);
3316 while(he) {
3317 struct connectdata *conn;
3318
3319 bundle = he->ptr;
3320
3321 curr = bundle->conn_list.head;
3322 while(curr) {
3323 conn = curr->ptr;
3324
3325 if(!conn->inuse) {
3326 /* Set higher score for the age passed since the connection was used */
3327 score = Curl_tvdiff(now, conn->now);
3328
3329 if(score > highscore) {
3330 highscore = score;
3331 conn_candidate = conn;
3332 }
3333 }
3334 curr = curr->next;
3335 }
3336
3337 he = Curl_hash_next_element(&iter);
3338 }
3339
3340 return conn_candidate;
3341}

3397/*
3398 * This function checks if given connection is dead and disconnects if so.
3399 * (That also removes it from the connection cache.)
3400 *
3401 * Returns TRUE if the connection actually was dead and disconnected.
3402 */
3403static bool disconnect_if_dead(struct connectdata *conn,
3404 struct Curl_easy *data)
3405{
3406 size_t pipeLen = conn->send_pipe.size + conn->recv_pipe.size;
3407 if(!pipeLen && !conn->inuse) {
3408 /* The check for a dead socket makes sense only if there are no
3409 handles in pipeline and the connection isn't already marked in
3410 use */
3411 bool dead;
3412
3413 if(conn->handler->connection_check) {
3414 /* The protocol has a special method for checking the state of the
3415 connection. Use it to check if the connection is dead. */
3416 unsigned int state;
3417
3418 state = conn->handler->connection_check(conn, CONNCHECK_ISDEAD);
3419 dead = (state & CONNRESULT_DEAD);
3420 }
3421 else {
3422 /* Use the general method for determining the death of a connection */
3423 dead = SocketIsDead(conn->sock[FIRSTSOCKET]);
3424 }
3425
3426 if(dead) {
3427 conn->data = data;
3428 infof(data, "Connection %ld seems to be dead!\n", conn->connection_id);
3429
3430 /* disconnect resources */
3431 Curl_disconnect(conn, /* dead_connection */TRUE);
3432 return TRUE;
3433 }
3434 }
3435 return FALSE;
3436}
3437
3438/*
3439 * Wrapper to use disconnect_if_dead() function in Curl_conncache_foreach()
3440 *
3441 * Returns always 0.
3442 */
3443static int call_disconnect_if_dead(struct connectdata *conn,
3444 void *param)
3445{
3446 struct Curl_easy* data = (struct Curl_easy*)param;
3447 disconnect_if_dead(conn, data);
3448 return 0; /* continue iteration */
3449}

3451/*
3452 * This function scans the connection cache for half-open/dead connections,
3453 * closes and removes them.
3454 * The cleanup is done at most once per second.
3455 */
3456static void prune_dead_connections(struct Curl_easy *data)
3457{
3458 struct curltime now = Curl_tvnow();
3459 time_t elapsed = Curl_tvdiff(now, data->state.conn_cache->last_cleanup);
3460
3461 if(elapsed >= 1000L) {
3462 Curl_conncache_foreach(data->state.conn_cache, data,
3463 call_disconnect_if_dead);
3464 data->state.conn_cache->last_cleanup = now;
3465 }
3466}

3469static size_t max_pipeline_length(struct Curl_multi *multi)
3470{
3471 return multi ? multi->max_pipeline_length : 0;
3472}

3474
3475/*
3476 * Given one filled in connection struct (named needle), this function should
3477 * detect if there already is one that has all the significant details
3478 * exactly the same and thus should be used instead.
3479 *
3480 * If there is a match, this function returns TRUE - and has marked the
3481 * connection as 'in-use'. It must later be called with ConnectionDone() to
3482 * return back to 'idle' (unused) state.
3483 *
3484 * The force_reuse flag is set if the connection must be used, even if
3485 * the pipelining strategy wants to open a new connection instead of reusing.
3486 */
3487static bool
3488ConnectionExists(struct Curl_easy *data,
3489 struct connectdata *needle,
3490 struct connectdata **usethis,
3491 bool *force_reuse,
3492 bool *waitpipe)
3493{
3494 struct connectdata *check;
3495 struct connectdata *chosen = 0;
3496 bool foundPendingCandidate = FALSE;
3497 int canpipe = IsPipeliningPossible(data, needle);
3498 struct connectbundle *bundle;
3499
3500#ifdef USE_NTLM
3501 bool wantNTLMhttp = ((data->state.authhost.want &
3502 (CURLAUTH_NTLM | CURLAUTH_NTLM_WB)) &&
3503 (needle->handler->protocol & PROTO_FAMILY_HTTP));
3504 bool wantProxyNTLMhttp = (needle->bits.proxy_user_passwd &&
3505 ((data->state.authproxy.want &
3506 (CURLAUTH_NTLM | CURLAUTH_NTLM_WB)) &&
3507 (needle->handler->protocol & PROTO_FAMILY_HTTP)));
3508#endif
3509
3510 *force_reuse = FALSE;
3511 *waitpipe = FALSE;
3512
3513 /* We can't pipeline if the site is blacklisted */
3514 if((canpipe & CURLPIPE_HTTP1) &&
3515 Curl_pipeline_site_blacklisted(data, needle))
3516 canpipe &= ~ CURLPIPE_HTTP1;
3517
3518 /* Look up the bundle with all the connections to this
3519 particular host */
3520 bundle = Curl_conncache_find_bundle(needle, data->state.conn_cache);
3521 if(bundle) {
3522 /* Max pipe length is zero (unlimited) for multiplexed connections */
3523 size_t max_pipe_len = (bundle->multiuse != BUNDLE_MULTIPLEX)?
3524 max_pipeline_length(data->multi):0;
3525 size_t best_pipe_len = max_pipe_len;
3526 struct curl_llist_element *curr;
3527
3528 infof(data, "Found bundle for host %s: %p [%s]\n",
3529 (needle->bits.conn_to_host ? needle->conn_to_host.name :
3530 needle->host.name), (void *)bundle,
3531 (bundle->multiuse == BUNDLE_PIPELINING ?
3532 "can pipeline" :
3533 (bundle->multiuse == BUNDLE_MULTIPLEX ?
3534 "can multiplex" : "serially")));
3535
3536 /* We can't pipeline if we don't know anything about the server */
3537 if(canpipe) {
3538 if(bundle->multiuse <= BUNDLE_UNKNOWN) {
3539 if((bundle->multiuse == BUNDLE_UNKNOWN) && data->set.pipewait) {
3540 infof(data, "Server doesn't support multi-use yet, wait\n");
3541 *waitpipe = TRUE;
3542 return FALSE; /* no re-use */
3543 }
3544
3545 infof(data, "Server doesn't support multi-use (yet)\n");
3546 canpipe = 0;
3547 }
3548 if((bundle->multiuse == BUNDLE_PIPELINING) &&
3549 !Curl_pipeline_wanted(data->multi, CURLPIPE_HTTP1)) {
3550 /* not asked for, switch off */
3551 infof(data, "Could pipeline, but not asked to!\n");
3552 canpipe = 0;
3553 }
3554 else if((bundle->multiuse == BUNDLE_MULTIPLEX) &&
3555 !Curl_pipeline_wanted(data->multi, CURLPIPE_MULTIPLEX)) {
3556 infof(data, "Could multiplex, but not asked to!\n");
3557 canpipe = 0;
3558 }
3559 }
3560
3561 curr = bundle->conn_list.head;
3562 while(curr) {
3563 bool match = FALSE;
3564 size_t pipeLen;
3565
3566 /*
3567 * Note that if we use a HTTP proxy in normal mode (no tunneling), we
3568 * check connections to that proxy and not to the actual remote server.
3569 */
3570 check = curr->ptr;
3571 curr = curr->next;
3572
3573 if(disconnect_if_dead(check, data))
3574 continue;
3575
3576 pipeLen = check->send_pipe.size + check->recv_pipe.size;
3577
3578 if(canpipe) {
3579 if(check->bits.protoconnstart && check->bits.close)
3580 continue;
3581
3582 if(!check->bits.multiplex) {
3583 /* If not multiplexing, make sure the connection is fine for HTTP/1
3584 pipelining */
3585 struct Curl_easy* sh = gethandleathead(&check->send_pipe);
3586 struct Curl_easy* rh = gethandleathead(&check->recv_pipe);
3587 if(sh) {
3588 if(!(IsPipeliningPossible(sh, check) & CURLPIPE_HTTP1))
3589 continue;
3590 }
3591 else if(rh) {
3592 if(!(IsPipeliningPossible(rh, check) & CURLPIPE_HTTP1))
3593 continue;
3594 }
3595 }
3596 }
3597 else {
3598 if(pipeLen > 0) {
3599 /* can only happen within multi handles, and means that another easy
3600 handle is using this connection */
3601 continue;
3602 }
3603
3604 if(Curl_resolver_asynch()) {
3605 /* ip_addr_str[0] is NUL only if the resolving of the name hasn't
3606 completed yet and until then we don't re-use this connection */
3607 if(!check->ip_addr_str[0]) {
3608 infof(data,
3609 "Connection #%ld is still name resolving, can't reuse\n",
3610 check->connection_id);
3611 continue;
3612 }
3613 }
3614
3615 if((check->sock[FIRSTSOCKET] == CURL_SOCKET_BAD) ||
3616 check->bits.close) {
3617 if(!check->bits.close)
3618 foundPendingCandidate = TRUE;
3619 /* Don't pick a connection that hasn't connected yet or that is going
3620 to get closed. */
3621 infof(data, "Connection #%ld isn't open enough, can't reuse\n",
3622 check->connection_id);
3623#ifdef DEBUGBUILD
3624 if(check->recv_pipe.size > 0) {
3625 infof(data,
3626 "BAD! Unconnected #%ld has a non-empty recv pipeline!\n",
3627 check->connection_id);
3628 }
3629#endif
3630 continue;
3631 }
3632 }
3633
3634#ifdef USE_UNIX_SOCKETS
3635 if(needle->unix_domain_socket) {
3636 if(!check->unix_domain_socket)
3637 continue;
3638 if(strcmp(needle->unix_domain_socket, check->unix_domain_socket))
3639 continue;
3640 if(needle->abstract_unix_socket != check->abstract_unix_socket)
3641 continue;
3642 }
3643 else if(check->unix_domain_socket)
3644 continue;
3645#endif
3646
3647 if((needle->handler->flags&PROTOPT_SSL) !=
3648 (check->handler->flags&PROTOPT_SSL))
3649 /* don't do mixed SSL and non-SSL connections */
3650 if(get_protocol_family(check->handler->protocol) !=
3651 needle->handler->protocol || !check->tls_upgraded)
3652 /* except protocols that have been upgraded via TLS */
3653 continue;
3654
3655 if(needle->bits.httpproxy != check->bits.httpproxy ||
3656 needle->bits.socksproxy != check->bits.socksproxy)
3657 continue;
3658
3659 if(needle->bits.socksproxy && !proxy_info_matches(&needle->socks_proxy,
3660 &check->socks_proxy))
3661 continue;
3662
3663 if(needle->bits.conn_to_host != check->bits.conn_to_host)
3664 /* don't mix connections that use the "connect to host" feature and
3665 * connections that don't use this feature */
3666 continue;
3667
3668 if(needle->bits.conn_to_port != check->bits.conn_to_port)
3669 /* don't mix connections that use the "connect to port" feature and
3670 * connections that don't use this feature */
3671 continue;
3672
3673 if(needle->bits.httpproxy) {
3674 if(!proxy_info_matches(&needle->http_proxy, &check->http_proxy))
3675 continue;
3676
3677 if(needle->bits.tunnel_proxy != check->bits.tunnel_proxy)
3678 continue;
3679
3680 if(needle->http_proxy.proxytype == CURLPROXY_HTTPS) {
3681 /* use https proxy */
3682 if(needle->handler->flags&PROTOPT_SSL) {
3683 /* use double layer ssl */
3684 if(!Curl_ssl_config_matches(&needle->proxy_ssl_config,
3685 &check->proxy_ssl_config))
3686 continue;
3687 if(check->proxy_ssl[FIRSTSOCKET].state != ssl_connection_complete)
3688 continue;
3689 }
3690 else {
3691 if(!Curl_ssl_config_matches(&needle->ssl_config,
3692 &check->ssl_config))
3693 continue;
3694 if(check->ssl[FIRSTSOCKET].state != ssl_connection_complete)
3695 continue;
3696 }
3697 }
3698 }
3699
3700 if(!canpipe && check->inuse)
3701 /* this request can't be pipelined but the checked connection is
3702 already in use so we skip it */
3703 continue;
3704
3705 if(needle->localdev || needle->localport) {
3706 /* If we are bound to a specific local end (IP+port), we must not
3707 re-use a random other one, although if we didn't ask for a
3708 particular one we can reuse one that was bound.
3709
3710 This comparison is a bit rough and too strict. Since the input
3711 parameters can be specified in numerous ways and still end up the
3712 same it would take a lot of processing to make it really accurate.
3713 Instead, this matching will assume that re-uses of bound connections
3714 will most likely also re-use the exact same binding parameters and
3715 missing out a few edge cases shouldn't hurt anyone very much.
3716 */
3717 if((check->localport != needle->localport) ||
3718 (check->localportrange != needle->localportrange) ||
3719 (needle->localdev &&
3720 (!check->localdev || strcmp(check->localdev, needle->localdev))))
3721 continue;
3722 }
3723
3724 if(!(needle->handler->flags & PROTOPT_CREDSPERREQUEST)) {
3725 /* This protocol requires credentials per connection,
3726 so verify that we're using the same name and password as well */
3727 if(strcmp(needle->user, check->user) ||
3728 strcmp(needle->passwd, check->passwd)) {
3729 /* one of them was different */
3730 continue;
3731 }
3732 }
3733
3734 if(!needle->bits.httpproxy || (needle->handler->flags&PROTOPT_SSL) ||
3735 needle->bits.tunnel_proxy) {
3736 /* The requested connection does not use a HTTP proxy or it uses SSL or
3737 it is a non-SSL protocol tunneled or it is a non-SSL protocol which
3738 is allowed to be upgraded via TLS */
3739
3740 if((strcasecompare(needle->handler->scheme, check->handler->scheme) ||
3741 (get_protocol_family(check->handler->protocol) ==
3742 needle->handler->protocol && check->tls_upgraded)) &&
3743 (!needle->bits.conn_to_host || strcasecompare(
3744 needle->conn_to_host.name, check->conn_to_host.name)) &&
3745 (!needle->bits.conn_to_port ||
3746 needle->conn_to_port == check->conn_to_port) &&
3747 strcasecompare(needle->host.name, check->host.name) &&
3748 needle->remote_port == check->remote_port) {
3749 /* The schemes match or the the protocol family is the same and the
3750 previous connection was TLS upgraded, and the hostname and host
3751 port match */
3752 if(needle->handler->flags & PROTOPT_SSL) {
3753 /* This is a SSL connection so verify that we're using the same
3754 SSL options as well */
3755 if(!Curl_ssl_config_matches(&needle->ssl_config,
3756 &check->ssl_config)) {
3757 DEBUGF(infof(data,
3758 "Connection #%ld has different SSL parameters, "
3759 "can't reuse\n",
3760 check->connection_id));
3761 continue;
3762 }
3763 if(check->ssl[FIRSTSOCKET].state != ssl_connection_complete) {
3764 foundPendingCandidate = TRUE;
3765 DEBUGF(infof(data,
3766 "Connection #%ld has not started SSL connect, "
3767 "can't reuse\n",
3768 check->connection_id));
3769 continue;
3770 }
3771 }
3772 match = TRUE;
3773 }
3774 }
3775 else {
3776 /* The requested connection is using the same HTTP proxy in normal
3777 mode (no tunneling) */
3778 match = TRUE;
3779 }
3780
3781 if(match) {
3782#if defined(USE_NTLM)
3783 /* If we are looking for an HTTP+NTLM connection, check if this is
3784 already authenticating with the right credentials. If not, keep
3785 looking so that we can reuse NTLM connections if
3786 possible. (Especially we must not reuse the same connection if
3787 partway through a handshake!) */
3788 if(wantNTLMhttp) {
3789 if(strcmp(needle->user, check->user) ||
3790 strcmp(needle->passwd, check->passwd))
3791 continue;
3792 }
3793 else if(check->ntlm.state != NTLMSTATE_NONE) {
3794 /* Connection is using NTLM auth but we don't want NTLM */
3795 continue;
3796 }
3797
3798 /* Same for Proxy NTLM authentication */
3799 if(wantProxyNTLMhttp) {
3800 /* Both check->http_proxy.user and check->http_proxy.passwd can be
3801 * NULL */
3802 if(!check->http_proxy.user || !check->http_proxy.passwd)
3803 continue;
3804
3805 if(strcmp(needle->http_proxy.user, check->http_proxy.user) ||
3806 strcmp(needle->http_proxy.passwd, check->http_proxy.passwd))
3807 continue;
3808 }
3809 else if(check->proxyntlm.state != NTLMSTATE_NONE) {
3810 /* Proxy connection is using NTLM auth but we don't want NTLM */
3811 continue;
3812 }
3813
3814 if(wantNTLMhttp || wantProxyNTLMhttp) {
3815 /* Credentials are already checked, we can use this connection */
3816 chosen = check;
3817
3818 if((wantNTLMhttp &&
3819 (check->ntlm.state != NTLMSTATE_NONE)) ||
3820 (wantProxyNTLMhttp &&
3821 (check->proxyntlm.state != NTLMSTATE_NONE))) {
3822 /* We must use this connection, no other */
3823 *force_reuse = TRUE;
3824 break;
3825 }
3826
3827 /* Continue look up for a better connection */
3828 continue;
3829 }
3830#endif
3831 if(canpipe) {
3832 /* We can pipeline if we want to. Let's continue looking for
3833 the optimal connection to use, i.e the shortest pipe that is not
3834 blacklisted. */
3835
3836 if(pipeLen == 0) {
3837 /* We have the optimal connection. Let's stop looking. */
3838 chosen = check;
3839 break;
3840 }
3841
3842 /* We can't use the connection if the pipe is full */
3843 if(max_pipe_len && (pipeLen >= max_pipe_len)) {
3844 infof(data, "Pipe is full, skip (%zu)\n", pipeLen);
3845 continue;
3846 }
3847#ifdef USE_NGHTTP2
3848 /* If multiplexed, make sure we don't go over concurrency limit */
3849 if(check->bits.multiplex) {
3850 /* Multiplexed connections can only be HTTP/2 for now */
3851 struct http_conn *httpc = &check->proto.httpc;
3852 if(pipeLen >= httpc->settings.max_concurrent_streams) {
3853 infof(data, "MAX_CONCURRENT_STREAMS reached, skip (%zu)\n",
3854 pipeLen);
3855 continue;
3856 }
3857 }
3858#endif
3859 /* We can't use the connection if the pipe is penalized */
3860 if(Curl_pipeline_penalized(data, check)) {
3861 infof(data, "Penalized, skip\n");
3862 continue;
3863 }
3864
3865 if(max_pipe_len) {
3866 if(pipeLen < best_pipe_len) {
3867 /* This connection has a shorter pipe so far. We'll pick this
3868 and continue searching */
3869 chosen = check;
3870 best_pipe_len = pipeLen;
3871 continue;
3872 }
3873 }
3874 else {
3875 /* When not pipelining (== multiplexed), we have a match here! */
3876 chosen = check;
3877 infof(data, "Multiplexed connection found!\n");
3878 break;
3879 }
3880 }
3881 else {
3882 /* We have found a connection. Let's stop searching. */
3883 chosen = check;
3884 break;
3885 }
3886 }
3887 }
3888 }
3889
3890 if(chosen) {
3891 *usethis = chosen;
3892 return TRUE; /* yes, we found one to use! */
3893 }
3894
3895 if(foundPendingCandidate && data->set.pipewait) {
3896 infof(data,
3897 "Found pending candidate for reuse and CURLOPT_PIPEWAIT is set\n");
3898 *waitpipe = TRUE;
3899 }
3900
3901 return FALSE; /* no matching connecting exists */
3902}
3903
3904/* after a TCP connection to the proxy has been verified, this function does
3905 the next magic step.
3906
3907 Note: this function's sub-functions call failf()
3908
3909*/
3910CURLcode Curl_connected_proxy(struct connectdata *conn, int sockindex)
3911{
3912 CURLcode result = CURLE_OK;
3913
3914 if(conn->bits.socksproxy) {
3915#ifndef CURL_DISABLE_PROXY
3916 /* for the secondary socket (FTP), use the "connect to host"
3917 * but ignore the "connect to port" (use the secondary port)
3918 */
3919 const char * const host = conn->bits.httpproxy ?
3920 conn->http_proxy.host.name :
3921 conn->bits.conn_to_host ?
3922 conn->conn_to_host.name :
3923 sockindex == SECONDARYSOCKET ?
3924 conn->secondaryhostname : conn->host.name;
3925 const int port = conn->bits.httpproxy ? (int)conn->http_proxy.port :
3926 sockindex == SECONDARYSOCKET ? conn->secondary_port :
3927 conn->bits.conn_to_port ? conn->conn_to_port :
3928 conn->remote_port;
3929 conn->bits.socksproxy_connecting = TRUE;
3930 switch(conn->socks_proxy.proxytype) {
3931 case CURLPROXY_SOCKS5:
3932 case CURLPROXY_SOCKS5_HOSTNAME:
3933 result = Curl_SOCKS5(conn->socks_proxy.user, conn->socks_proxy.passwd,
3934 host, port, sockindex, conn);
3935 break;
3936
3937 case CURLPROXY_SOCKS4:
3938 case CURLPROXY_SOCKS4A:
3939 result = Curl_SOCKS4(conn->socks_proxy.user, host, port, sockindex,
3940 conn);
3941 break;
3942
3943 default:
3944 failf(conn->data, "unknown proxytype option given");
3945 result = CURLE_COULDNT_CONNECT;
3946 } /* switch proxytype */
3947 conn->bits.socksproxy_connecting = FALSE;
3948#else
3949 (void)sockindex;
3950#endif /* CURL_DISABLE_PROXY */
3951 }
3952
3953 return result;
3954}

3990/*
3991 * We are doing protocol-specific connecting and this is being called over and
3992 * over from the multi interface until the connection phase is done on
3993 * protocol layer.
3994 */
3995
3996CURLcode Curl_protocol_connecting(struct connectdata *conn,
3997 bool *done)
3998{
3999 CURLcode result = CURLE_OK;
4000
4001 if(conn && conn->handler->connecting) {
4002 *done = FALSE;
4003 result = conn->handler->connecting(conn, done);
4004 }
4005 else
4006 *done = TRUE;
4007
4008 return result;
4009}

4011/*
4012 * We are DOING this is being called over and over from the multi interface
4013 * until the DOING phase is done on protocol layer.
4014 */
4015
4016CURLcode Curl_protocol_doing(struct connectdata *conn, bool *done)
4017{
4018 CURLcode result = CURLE_OK;
4019
4020 if(conn && conn->handler->doing) {
4021 *done = FALSE;
4022 result = conn->handler->doing(conn, done);
4023 }
4024 else
4025 *done = TRUE;
4026
4027 return result;
4028}

4030/*
4031 * We have discovered that the TCP connection has been successful, we can now
4032 * proceed with some action.
4033 *
4034 */
4035CURLcode Curl_protocol_connect(struct connectdata *conn,
4036 bool *protocol_done)
4037{
4038 CURLcode result = CURLE_OK;
4039
4040 *protocol_done = FALSE;
4041
4042 if(conn->bits.tcpconnect[FIRSTSOCKET] && conn->bits.protoconnstart) {
4043 /* We already are connected, get back. This may happen when the connect
4044 worked fine in the first call, like when we connect to a local server
4045 or proxy. Note that we don't know if the protocol is actually done.
4046
4047 Unless this protocol doesn't have any protocol-connect callback, as
4048 then we know we're done. */
4049 if(!conn->handler->connecting)
4050 *protocol_done = TRUE;
4051
4052 return CURLE_OK;
4053 }
4054
4055 if(!conn->bits.protoconnstart) {
4056
4057 result = Curl_proxy_connect(conn, FIRSTSOCKET);
4058 if(result)
4059 return result;
4060
4061 if(CONNECT_FIRSTSOCKET_PROXY_SSL())
4062 /* wait for HTTPS proxy SSL initialization to complete */
4063 return CURLE_OK;
4064
4065 if(conn->bits.tunnel_proxy && conn->bits.httpproxy &&
4066 Curl_connect_ongoing(conn))
4067 /* when using an HTTP tunnel proxy, await complete tunnel establishment
4068 before proceeding further. Return CURLE_OK so we'll be called again */
4069 return CURLE_OK;
4070
4071 if(conn->handler->connect_it) {
4072 /* is there a protocol-specific connect() procedure? */
4073
4074 /* Call the protocol-specific connect function */
4075 result = conn->handler->connect_it(conn, protocol_done);
4076 }
4077 else
4078 *protocol_done = TRUE;
4079
4080 /* it has started, possibly even completed but that knowledge isn't stored
4081 in this bit! */
4082 if(!result)
4083 conn->bits.protoconnstart = TRUE;
4084 }
4085
4086 return result; /* pass back status */
4087}

4089/*
4090 * Helpers for IDNA conversions.
4091 */
4092static bool is_ASCII_name(const char *hostname)
4093{
4094 const unsigned char *ch = (const unsigned char *)hostname;
4095
4096 while(*ch) {
4097 if(*ch++ & 0x80)
4098 return FALSE;
4099 }
4100 return TRUE;
4101}

4103/*
4104 * Perform any necessary IDN conversion of hostname
4105 */
4106static void fix_hostname(struct connectdata *conn, struct hostname *host)
4107{
4108 size_t len;
4109 struct Curl_easy *data = conn->data;
4110
4111#ifndef USE_LIBIDN2
4112 (void)data;
4113 (void)conn;
4114#elif defined(CURL_DISABLE_VERBOSE_STRINGS)
4115 (void)conn;
4116#endif
4117
4118 /* set the name we use to display the host name */
4119 host->dispname = host->name;
4120
4121 len = strlen(host->name);
4122 if(len && (host->name[len-1] == '.'))
4123 /* strip off a single trailing dot if present, primarily for SNI but
4124 there's no use for it */
4125 host->name[len-1] = 0;
4126
4127 /* Check name for non-ASCII and convert hostname to ACE form if we can */
4128 if(!is_ASCII_name(host->name)) {
4129#ifdef USE_LIBIDN2
4130 if(idn2_check_version(IDN2_VERSION)) {
4131 char *ace_hostname = NULL;
4132#if IDN2_VERSION_NUMBER >= 0x00140000
4133 /* IDN2_NFC_INPUT: Normalize input string using normalization form C.
4134 IDN2_NONTRANSITIONAL: Perform Unicode TR46 non-transitional
4135 processing. */
4136 int flags = IDN2_NFC_INPUT | IDN2_NONTRANSITIONAL;
4137#else
4138 int flags = IDN2_NFC_INPUT;
4139#endif
4140 int rc = idn2_lookup_ul((const char *)host->name, &ace_hostname, flags);
4141 if(rc == IDN2_OK) {
4142 host->encalloc = (char *)ace_hostname;
4143 /* change the name pointer to point to the encoded hostname */
4144 host->name = host->encalloc;
4145 }
4146 else
4147 infof(data, "Failed to convert %s to ACE; %s\n", host->name,
4148 idn2_strerror(rc));
4149 }
4150#elif defined(USE_WIN32_IDN)
4151 char *ace_hostname = NULL;
4152
4153 if(curl_win32_idn_to_ascii(host->name, &ace_hostname)) {
4154 host->encalloc = ace_hostname;
4155 /* change the name pointer to point to the encoded hostname */
4156 host->name = host->encalloc;
4157 }
4158 else
4159 infof(data, "Failed to convert %s to ACE;\n", host->name);
4160#else
4161 infof(data, "IDN support not present, can't parse Unicode domains\n");
4162#endif
4163 }
4164}

4193/*
4194 * Allocate and initialize a new connectdata object.
4195 */
4196static struct connectdata *allocate_conn(struct Curl_easy *data)
4197{
4198#ifdef USE_SSL
4199#define SSL_EXTRA + 4 * Curl_ssl->sizeof_ssl_backend_data - sizeof(long long)
4200#else
4201#define SSL_EXTRA 0
4202#endif
4203 struct connectdata *conn = calloc(1, sizeof(struct connectdata) + SSL_EXTRA);
4204 if(!conn)
4205 return NULL;
4206
4207 conn->handler = &Curl_handler_dummy; /* Be sure we have a handler defined
4208 already from start to avoid NULL
4209 situations and checks */
4210
4211 /* and we setup a few fields in case we end up actually using this struct */
4212
4213 conn->sock[FIRSTSOCKET] = CURL_SOCKET_BAD; /* no file descriptor */
4214 conn->sock[SECONDARYSOCKET] = CURL_SOCKET_BAD; /* no file descriptor */
4215 conn->tempsock[0] = CURL_SOCKET_BAD; /* no file descriptor */
4216 conn->tempsock[1] = CURL_SOCKET_BAD; /* no file descriptor */
4217 conn->connection_id = -1; /* no ID */
4218 conn->port = -1; /* unknown at this point */
4219 conn->remote_port = -1; /* unknown at this point */
4220#if defined(USE_RECV_BEFORE_SEND_WORKAROUND) && defined(DEBUGBUILD)
4221 conn->postponed[0].bindsock = CURL_SOCKET_BAD; /* no file descriptor */
4222 conn->postponed[1].bindsock = CURL_SOCKET_BAD; /* no file descriptor */
4223#endif /* USE_RECV_BEFORE_SEND_WORKAROUND && DEBUGBUILD */
4224
4225 /* Default protocol-independent behavior doesn't support persistent
4226 connections, so we set this to force-close. Protocols that support
4227 this need to set this to FALSE in their "curl_do" functions. */
4228 connclose(conn, "Default to force-close");
4229
4230 /* Store creation time to help future close decision making */
4231 conn->created = Curl_tvnow();
4232
4233 conn->data = data; /* Setup the association between this connection
4234 and the Curl_easy */
4235
4236 conn->http_proxy.proxytype = data->set.proxytype;
4237 conn->socks_proxy.proxytype = CURLPROXY_SOCKS4;
4238
4239#ifdef CURL_DISABLE_PROXY
4240
4241 conn->bits.proxy = FALSE;
4242 conn->bits.httpproxy = FALSE;
4243 conn->bits.socksproxy = FALSE;
4244 conn->bits.proxy_user_passwd = FALSE;
4245 conn->bits.tunnel_proxy = FALSE;
4246
4247#else /* CURL_DISABLE_PROXY */
4248
4249 /* note that these two proxy bits are now just on what looks to be
4250 requested, they may be altered down the road */
4251 conn->bits.proxy = (data->set.str[STRING_PROXY] &&
4252 *data->set.str[STRING_PROXY]) ? TRUE : FALSE;
4253 conn->bits.httpproxy = (conn->bits.proxy &&
4254 (conn->http_proxy.proxytype == CURLPROXY_HTTP ||
4255 conn->http_proxy.proxytype == CURLPROXY_HTTP_1_0 ||
4256 conn->http_proxy.proxytype == CURLPROXY_HTTPS)) ?
4257 TRUE : FALSE;
4258 conn->bits.socksproxy = (conn->bits.proxy &&
4259 !conn->bits.httpproxy) ? TRUE : FALSE;
4260
4261 if(data->set.str[STRING_PRE_PROXY] && *data->set.str[STRING_PRE_PROXY]) {
4262 conn->bits.proxy = TRUE;
4263 conn->bits.socksproxy = TRUE;
4264 }
4265
4266 conn->bits.proxy_user_passwd =
4267 (data->set.str[STRING_PROXYUSERNAME]) ? TRUE : FALSE;
4268 conn->bits.tunnel_proxy = data->set.tunnel_thru_httpproxy;
4269
4270#endif /* CURL_DISABLE_PROXY */
4271
4272 conn->bits.user_passwd = (data->set.str[STRING_USERNAME]) ? TRUE : FALSE;
4273 conn->bits.ftp_use_epsv = data->set.ftp_use_epsv;
4274 conn->bits.ftp_use_eprt = data->set.ftp_use_eprt;
4275
4276 conn->ssl_config.verifystatus = data->set.ssl.primary.verifystatus;
4277 conn->ssl_config.verifypeer = data->set.ssl.primary.verifypeer;
4278 conn->ssl_config.verifyhost = data->set.ssl.primary.verifyhost;
4279 conn->proxy_ssl_config.verifystatus =
4280 data->set.proxy_ssl.primary.verifystatus;
4281 conn->proxy_ssl_config.verifypeer = data->set.proxy_ssl.primary.verifypeer;
4282 conn->proxy_ssl_config.verifyhost = data->set.proxy_ssl.primary.verifyhost;
4283
4284 conn->ip_version = data->set.ipver;
4285
4286#ifdef USE_SSL
4287 /*
4288 * To save on malloc()s, the SSL backend-specific data has been allocated
4289 * at the end of the connectdata struct.
4290 */
4291 {
4292 char *p = (char *)&conn->align_data__do_not_use;
4293 conn->ssl[0].backend = (struct ssl_backend_data *)p;
4294 conn->ssl[1].backend =
4295 (struct ssl_backend_data *)(p + Curl_ssl->sizeof_ssl_backend_data);
4296 conn->proxy_ssl[0].backend =
4297 (struct ssl_backend_data *)(p + Curl_ssl->sizeof_ssl_backend_data * 2);
4298 conn->proxy_ssl[1].backend =
4299 (struct ssl_backend_data *)(p + Curl_ssl->sizeof_ssl_backend_data * 3);
4300 }
4301#endif
4302
4303#if !defined(CURL_DISABLE_HTTP) && defined(USE_NTLM) && \
4304 defined(NTLM_WB_ENABLED)
4305 conn->ntlm_auth_hlpr_socket = CURL_SOCKET_BAD;
4306 conn->ntlm_auth_hlpr_pid = 0;
4307 conn->challenge_header = NULL;
4308 conn->response_header = NULL;
4309#endif
4310
4311 if(Curl_pipeline_wanted(data->multi, CURLPIPE_HTTP1) &&
4312 !conn->master_buffer) {
4313 /* Allocate master_buffer to be used for HTTP/1 pipelining */
4314 conn->master_buffer = calloc(MASTERBUF_SIZE, sizeof(char));
4315 if(!conn->master_buffer)
4316 goto error;
4317 }
4318
4319 /* Initialize the pipeline lists */
4320 Curl_llist_init(&conn->send_pipe, (curl_llist_dtor) llist_dtor);
4321 Curl_llist_init(&conn->recv_pipe, (curl_llist_dtor) llist_dtor);
4322
4323#ifdef HAVE_GSSAPI
4324 conn->data_prot = PROT_CLEAR;
4325#endif
4326
4327 /* Store the local bind parameters that will be used for this connection */
4328 if(data->set.str[STRING_DEVICE]) {
4329 conn->localdev = strdup(data->set.str[STRING_DEVICE]);
4330 if(!conn->localdev)
4331 goto error;
4332 }
4333 conn->localportrange = data->set.localportrange;
4334 conn->localport = data->set.localport;
4335
4336 /* the close socket stuff needs to be copied to the connection struct as
4337 it may live on without (this specific) Curl_easy */
4338 conn->fclosesocket = data->set.fclosesocket;
4339 conn->closesocket_client = data->set.closesocket_client;
4340
4341 return conn;
4342 error:
4343
4344 Curl_llist_destroy(&conn->send_pipe, NULL);
4345 Curl_llist_destroy(&conn->recv_pipe, NULL);
4346
4347 free(conn->master_buffer);
4348 free(conn->localdev);
4349 free(conn);
4350 return NULL;
4351}
4352
4353static CURLcode findprotocol(struct Curl_easy *data,
4354 struct connectdata *conn,
4355 const char *protostr)
4356{
4357 const struct Curl_handler * const *pp;
4358 const struct Curl_handler *p;
4359
4360 /* Scan protocol handler table and match against 'protostr' to set a few
4361 variables based on the URL. Now that the handler may be changed later
4362 when the protocol specific setup function is called. */
4363 for(pp = protocols; (p = *pp) != NULL; pp++) {
4364 if(strcasecompare(p->scheme, protostr)) {
4365 /* Protocol found in table. Check if allowed */
4366 if(!(data->set.allowed_protocols & p->protocol))
4367 /* nope, get out */
4368 break;
4369
4370 /* it is allowed for "normal" request, now do an extra check if this is
4371 the result of a redirect */
4372 if(data->state.this_is_a_follow &&
4373 !(data->set.redir_protocols & p->protocol))
4374 /* nope, get out */
4375 break;
4376
4377 /* Perform setup complement if some. */
4378 conn->handler = conn->given = p;
4379
4380 /* 'port' and 'remote_port' are set in setup_connection_internals() */
4381 return CURLE_OK;
4382 }
4383 }
4384
4385
4386 /* The protocol was not found in the table, but we don't have to assign it
4387 to anything since it is already assigned to a dummy-struct in the
4388 create_conn() function when the connectdata struct is allocated. */
4389 failf(data, "Protocol \"%s\" not supported or disabled in " LIBCURL_NAME,
4390 protostr);
4391
4392 return CURLE_UNSUPPORTED_PROTOCOL;
4393}
4394
4395/*
4396 * Parse URL and fill in the relevant members of the connection struct.
4397 */
4398static CURLcode parseurlandfillconn(struct Curl_easy *data,
4399 struct connectdata *conn,
4400 bool *prot_missing,
4401 char **userp, char **passwdp,
4402 char **optionsp)
4403{
4404 char *at;
4405 char *fragment;
4406 char *path = data->state.path;
4407 char *query;
4408 int i;
4409 int rc;
4410 const char *protop = "";
4411 CURLcode result;
4412 bool rebuild_url = FALSE;
4413 bool url_has_scheme = FALSE;
4414 char protobuf[16];
4415
4416 *prot_missing = FALSE;
4417
4418 /* We might pass the entire URL into the request so we need to make sure
4419 * there are no bad characters in there.*/
4420 if(strpbrk(data->change.url, "\r\n")) {
4421 failf(data, "Illegal characters found in URL");
4422 return CURLE_URL_MALFORMAT;
4423 }
4424
4425 /*************************************************************
4426 * Parse the URL.
4427 *
4428 * We need to parse the url even when using the proxy, because we will need
4429 * the hostname and port in case we are trying to SSL connect through the
4430 * proxy -- and we don't know if we will need to use SSL until we parse the
4431 * url ...
4432 ************************************************************/
4433 if(data->change.url[0] == ':') {
4434 failf(data, "Bad URL, colon is first character");
4435 return CURLE_URL_MALFORMAT;
4436 }
4437
4438 /* MSDOS/Windows style drive prefix, eg c: in c:foo */
4439#define STARTS_WITH_DRIVE_PREFIX(str) \
4440 ((('a' <= str[0] && str[0] <= 'z') || \
4441 ('A' <= str[0] && str[0] <= 'Z')) && \
4442 (str[1] == ':'))
4443
4444 /* Don't mistake a drive letter for a scheme if the default protocol is file.
4445 curld --proto-default file c:/foo/bar.txt */
4446 if(STARTS_WITH_DRIVE_PREFIX(data->change.url) &&
4447 data->set.str[STRING_DEFAULT_PROTOCOL] &&
4448 strcasecompare(data->set.str[STRING_DEFAULT_PROTOCOL], "file")) {
4449 ; /* do nothing */
4450 }
4451 else { /* check for a scheme */
4452 for(i = 0; i < 16 && data->change.url[i]; ++i) {
4453 if(data->change.url[i] == '/')
4454 break;
4455 if(data->change.url[i] == ':') {
4456 url_has_scheme = TRUE;
4457 break;
4458 }
4459 }
4460 }
4461
4462 /* handle the file: scheme */
4463 if((url_has_scheme && strncasecompare(data->change.url, "file:", 5)) ||
4464 (!url_has_scheme && data->set.str[STRING_DEFAULT_PROTOCOL] &&
4465 strcasecompare(data->set.str[STRING_DEFAULT_PROTOCOL], "file"))) {
4466 if(url_has_scheme)
4467 rc = sscanf(data->change.url, "%*15[^\n/:]:%[^\n]", path);
4468 else
4469 rc = sscanf(data->change.url, "%[^\n]", path);
4470
4471 if(rc != 1) {
4472 failf(data, "Bad URL");
4473 return CURLE_URL_MALFORMAT;
4474 }
4475
4476 if(url_has_scheme && path[0] == '/' && path[1] == '/') {
4477 /* Allow omitted hostname (e.g. file:/<path>). This is not strictly
4478 * speaking a valid file: URL by RFC 1738, but treating file:/<path> as
4479 * file://localhost/<path> is similar to how other schemes treat missing
4480 * hostnames. See RFC 1808. */
4481
4482 /* This cannot be done with strcpy() in a portable manner, since the
4483 memory areas overlap! */
4484 memmove(path, path + 2, strlen(path + 2) + 1);
4485 }
4486
4487 /*
4488 * we deal with file://<host>/<path> differently since it supports no
4489 * hostname other than "localhost" and "127.0.0.1", which is unique among
4490 * the URL protocols specified in RFC 1738
4491 */
4492 if(path[0] != '/' && !STARTS_WITH_DRIVE_PREFIX(path)) {
4493 /* the URL includes a host name, it must match "localhost" or
4494 "127.0.0.1" to be valid */
4495 char *ptr;
4496 if(!checkprefix("localhost/", path) &&
4497 !checkprefix("127.0.0.1/", path)) {
4498 failf(data, "Invalid file://hostname/, "
4499 "expected localhost or 127.0.0.1 or none");
4500 return CURLE_URL_MALFORMAT;
4501 }
4502 ptr = &path[9]; /* now points to the slash after the host */
4503
4504 /* there was a host name and slash present
4505
4506 RFC1738 (section 3.1, page 5) says:
4507
4508 The rest of the locator consists of data specific to the scheme,
4509 and is known as the "url-path". It supplies the details of how the
4510 specified resource can be accessed. Note that the "/" between the
4511 host (or port) and the url-path is NOT part of the url-path.
4512
4513 As most agents use file://localhost/foo to get '/foo' although the
4514 slash preceding foo is a separator and not a slash for the path,
4515 a URL as file://localhost//foo must be valid as well, to refer to
4516 the same file with an absolute path.
4517 */
4518
4519 if('/' == ptr[1])
4520 /* if there was two slashes, we skip the first one as that is then
4521 used truly as a separator */
4522 ptr++;
4523
4524 /* This cannot be made with strcpy, as the memory chunks overlap! */
4525 memmove(path, ptr, strlen(ptr) + 1);
4526 }
4527
4528#if !defined(MSDOS) && !defined(WIN32) && !defined(__CYGWIN__)
4529 if(STARTS_WITH_DRIVE_PREFIX(path)) {
4530 failf(data, "File drive letters are only accepted in MSDOS/Windows.");
4531 return CURLE_URL_MALFORMAT;
4532 }
4533#endif
4534
4535 protop = "file"; /* protocol string */
4536 *prot_missing = !url_has_scheme;
4537 }
4538 else {
4539 /* clear path */
4540 char slashbuf[4];
4541 path[0] = 0;
4542
4543 rc = sscanf(data->change.url,
4544 "%15[^\n/:]:%3[/]%[^\n/?#]%[^\n]",
4545 protobuf, slashbuf, conn->host.name, path);
4546 if(2 == rc) {
4547 failf(data, "Bad URL");
4548 return CURLE_URL_MALFORMAT;
4549 }
4550 if(3 > rc) {
4551
4552 /*
4553 * The URL was badly formatted, let's try the browser-style _without_
4554 * protocol specified like 'http://'.
4555 */
4556 rc = sscanf(data->change.url, "%[^\n/?#]%[^\n]", conn->host.name, path);
4557 if(1 > rc) {
4558 /*
4559 * We couldn't even get this format.
4560 * djgpp 2.04 has a sscanf() bug where 'conn->host.name' is
4561 * assigned, but the return value is EOF!
4562 */
4563#if defined(__DJGPP__) && (DJGPP_MINOR == 4)
4564 if(!(rc == -1 && *conn->host.name))
4565#endif
4566 {
4567 failf(data, "<url> malformed");
4568 return CURLE_URL_MALFORMAT;
4569 }
4570 }
4571
4572 /*
4573 * Since there was no protocol part specified in the URL use the
4574 * user-specified default protocol. If we weren't given a default make a
4575 * guess by matching some protocols against the host's outermost
4576 * sub-domain name. Finally if there was no match use HTTP.
4577 */
4578
4579 protop = data->set.str[STRING_DEFAULT_PROTOCOL];
4580 if(!protop) {
4581 /* Note: if you add a new protocol, please update the list in
4582 * lib/version.c too! */
4583 if(checkprefix("FTP.", conn->host.name))
4584 protop = "ftp";
4585 else if(checkprefix("DICT.", conn->host.name))
4586 protop = "DICT";
4587 else if(checkprefix("LDAP.", conn->host.name))
4588 protop = "LDAP";
4589 else if(checkprefix("IMAP.", conn->host.name))
4590 protop = "IMAP";
4591 else if(checkprefix("SMTP.", conn->host.name))
4592 protop = "smtp";
4593 else if(checkprefix("POP3.", conn->host.name))
4594 protop = "pop3";
4595 else
4596 protop = "http";
4597 }
4598
4599 *prot_missing = TRUE; /* not given in URL */
4600 }
4601 else {
4602 size_t s = strlen(slashbuf);
4603 protop = protobuf;
4604 if(s != 2) {
4605 infof(data, "Unwillingly accepted illegal URL using %d slash%s!\n",
4606 s, s>1?"es":"");
4607
4608 if(data->change.url_alloc)
4609 free(data->change.url);
4610 /* repair the URL to use two slashes */
4611 data->change.url = aprintf("%s://%s%s",
4612 protobuf, conn->host.name, path);
4613 if(!data->change.url)
4614 return CURLE_OUT_OF_MEMORY;
4615 data->change.url_alloc = TRUE;
4616 }
4617 }
4618 }
4619
4620 /* We search for '?' in the host name (but only on the right side of a
4621 * @-letter to allow ?-letters in username and password) to handle things
4622 * like http://example.com?param= (notice the missing '/').
4623 */
4624 at = strchr(conn->host.name, '@');
4625 if(at)
4626 query = strchr(at + 1, '?');
4627 else
4628 query = strchr(conn->host.name, '?');
4629
4630 if(query) {
4631 /* We must insert a slash before the '?'-letter in the URL. If the URL had
4632 a slash after the '?', that is where the path currently begins and the
4633 '?string' is still part of the host name.
4634
4635 We must move the trailing part from the host name and put it first in
4636 the path. And have it all prefixed with a slash.
4637 */
4638
4639 size_t hostlen = strlen(query);
4640 size_t pathlen = strlen(path);
4641
4642 /* move the existing path plus the zero byte forward, to make room for
4643 the host-name part */
4644 memmove(path + hostlen + 1, path, pathlen + 1);
4645
4646 /* now copy the trailing host part in front of the existing path */
4647 memcpy(path + 1, query, hostlen);
4648
4649 path[0]='/'; /* prepend the missing slash */
4650 rebuild_url = TRUE;
4651
4652 *query = 0; /* now cut off the hostname at the ? */
4653 }
4654 else if(!path[0]) {
4655 /* if there's no path set, use a single slash */
4656 strcpy(path, "/");
4657 rebuild_url = TRUE;
4658 }
4659
4660 /* If the URL is malformatted (missing a '/' after hostname before path) we
4661 * insert a slash here. The only letters except '/' that can start a path is
4662 * '?' and '#' - as controlled by the two sscanf() patterns above.
4663 */
4664 if(path[0] != '/') {
4665 /* We need this function to deal with overlapping memory areas. We know
4666 that the memory area 'path' points to is 'urllen' bytes big and that
4667 is bigger than the path. Use +1 to move the zero byte too. */
4668 memmove(&path[1], path, strlen(path) + 1);
4669 path[0] = '/';
4670 rebuild_url = TRUE;
4671 }
4672 else if(!data->set.path_as_is) {
4673 /* sanitise paths and remove ../ and ./ sequences according to RFC3986 */
4674 char *newp = Curl_dedotdotify(path);
4675 if(!newp)
4676 return CURLE_OUT_OF_MEMORY;
4677
4678 if(strcmp(newp, path)) {
4679 rebuild_url = TRUE;
4680 free(data->state.pathbuffer);
4681 data->state.pathbuffer = newp;
4682 data->state.path = newp;
4683 path = newp;
4684 }
4685 else
4686 free(newp);
4687 }
4688
4689 /*
4690 * "rebuild_url" means that one or more URL components have been modified so
4691 * we need to generate an updated full version. We need the corrected URL
4692 * when communicating over HTTP proxy and we don't know at this point if
4693 * we're using a proxy or not.
4694 */
4695 if(rebuild_url) {
4696 char *reurl;
4697
4698 size_t plen = strlen(path); /* new path, should be 1 byte longer than
4699 the original */
4700 size_t prefixlen = strlen(conn->host.name);
4701
4702 if(!*prot_missing) {
4703 size_t protolen = strlen(protop);
4704
4705 if(curl_strnequal(protop, data->change.url, protolen))
4706 prefixlen += protolen;
4707 else {
4708 failf(data, "<url> malformed");
4709 return CURLE_URL_MALFORMAT;
4710 }
4711
4712 if(curl_strnequal("://", &data->change.url[protolen], 3))
4713 prefixlen += 3;
4714 /* only file: is allowed to omit one or both slashes */
4715 else if(curl_strnequal("file:", data->change.url, 5))
4716 prefixlen += 1 + (data->change.url[5] == '/');
4717 else {
4718 failf(data, "<url> malformed");
4719 return CURLE_URL_MALFORMAT;
4720 }
4721 }
4722
4723 reurl = malloc(prefixlen + plen + 1);
4724 if(!reurl)
4725 return CURLE_OUT_OF_MEMORY;
4726
4727 /* copy the prefix */
4728 memcpy(reurl, data->change.url, prefixlen);
4729
4730 /* append the trailing piece + zerobyte */
4731 memcpy(&reurl[prefixlen], path, plen + 1);
4732
4733 /* possible free the old one */
4734 if(data->change.url_alloc) {
4735 Curl_safefree(data->change.url);
4736 data->change.url_alloc = FALSE;
4737 }
4738
4739 infof(data, "Rebuilt URL to: %s\n", reurl);
4740
4741 data->change.url = reurl;
4742 data->change.url_alloc = TRUE; /* free this later */
4743 }
4744
4745 result = findprotocol(data, conn, protop);
4746 if(result)
4747 return result;
4748
4749 /*
4750 * Parse the login details from the URL and strip them out of
4751 * the host name
4752 */
4753 result = parse_url_login(data, conn, userp, passwdp, optionsp);
4754 if(result)
4755 return result;
4756
4757 if(conn->host.name[0] == '[') {
4758 /* This looks like an IPv6 address literal. See if there is an address
4759 scope if there is no location header */
4760 char *percent = strchr(conn->host.name, '%');
4761 if(percent) {
4762 unsigned int identifier_offset = 3;
4763 char *endp;
4764 unsigned long scope;
4765 if(strncmp("%25", percent, 3) != 0) {
4766 infof(data,
4767 "Please URL encode %% as %%25, see RFC 6874.\n");
4768 identifier_offset = 1;
4769 }
4770 scope = strtoul(percent + identifier_offset, &endp, 10);
4771 if(*endp == ']') {
4772 /* The address scope was well formed. Knock it out of the
4773 hostname. */
4774 memmove(percent, endp, strlen(endp) + 1);
4775 conn->scope_id = (unsigned int)scope;
4776 }
4777 else {
4778 /* Zone identifier is not numeric */
4779#if defined(HAVE_NET_IF_H) && defined(IFNAMSIZ) && defined(HAVE_IF_NAMETOINDEX)
4780 char ifname[IFNAMSIZ + 2];
4781 char *square_bracket;
4782 unsigned int scopeidx = 0;
4783 strncpy(ifname, percent + identifier_offset, IFNAMSIZ + 2);
4784 /* Ensure nullbyte termination */
4785 ifname[IFNAMSIZ + 1] = '\0';
4786 square_bracket = strchr(ifname, ']');
4787 if(square_bracket) {
4788 /* Remove ']' */
4789 *square_bracket = '\0';
4790 scopeidx = if_nametoindex(ifname);
4791 if(scopeidx == 0) {
4792 infof(data, "Invalid network interface: %s; %s\n", ifname,
4793 strerror(errno));
4794 }
4795 }
4796 if(scopeidx > 0) {
4797 char *p = percent + identifier_offset + strlen(ifname);
4798
4799 /* Remove zone identifier from hostname */
4800 memmove(percent, p, strlen(p) + 1);
4801 conn->scope_id = scopeidx;
4802 }
4803 else
4804#endif /* HAVE_NET_IF_H && IFNAMSIZ */
4805 infof(data, "Invalid IPv6 address format\n");
4806 }
4807 }
4808 }
4809
4810 if(data->set.scope_id)
4811 /* Override any scope that was set above. */
4812 conn->scope_id = data->set.scope_id;
4813
4814 /* Remove the fragment part of the path. Per RFC 2396, this is always the
4815 last part of the URI. We are looking for the first '#' so that we deal
4816 gracefully with non conformant URI such as http://example.com#foo#bar. */
4817 fragment = strchr(path, '#');
4818 if(fragment) {
4819 *fragment = 0;
4820
4821 /* we know the path part ended with a fragment, so we know the full URL
4822 string does too and we need to cut it off from there so it isn't used
4823 over proxy */
4824 fragment = strchr(data->change.url, '#');
4825 if(fragment)
4826 *fragment = 0;
4827 }
4828
4829 /*
4830 * So if the URL was A://B/C#D,
4831 * protop is A
4832 * conn->host.name is B
4833 * data->state.path is /C
4834 */
4835 return CURLE_OK;
4836}
4837
4838/*
4839 * If we're doing a resumed transfer, we need to setup our stuff
4840 * properly.
4841 */
4842static CURLcode setup_range(struct Curl_easy *data)
4843{
4844 struct UrlState *s = &data->state;
4845 s->resume_from = data->set.set_resume_from;
4846 if(s->resume_from || data->set.str[STRING_SET_RANGE]) {
4847 if(s->rangestringalloc)
4848 free(s->range);
4849
4850 if(s->resume_from)
4851 s->range = aprintf("%" CURL_FORMAT_CURL_OFF_TU "-", s->resume_from);
4852 else
4853 s->range = strdup(data->set.str[STRING_SET_RANGE]);
4854
4855 s->rangestringalloc = (s->range) ? TRUE : FALSE;
4856
4857 if(!s->range)
4858 return CURLE_OUT_OF_MEMORY;
4859
4860 /* tell ourselves to fetch this range */
4861 s->use_range = TRUE; /* enable range download */
4862 }
4863 else
4864 s->use_range = FALSE; /* disable range download */
4865
4866 return CURLE_OK;
4867}

4870/*
4871 * setup_connection_internals() -
4872 *
4873 * Setup connection internals specific to the requested protocol in the
4874 * Curl_easy. This is inited and setup before the connection is made but
4875 * is about the particular protocol that is to be used.
4876 *
4877 * This MUST get called after proxy magic has been figured out.
4878 */
4879static CURLcode setup_connection_internals(struct connectdata *conn)
4880{
4881 const struct Curl_handler * p;
4882 CURLcode result;
4883 struct Curl_easy *data = conn->data;
4884
4885 /* in some case in the multi state-machine, we go back to the CONNECT state
4886 and then a second (or third or...) call to this function will be made
4887 without doing a DISCONNECT or DONE in between (since the connection is
4888 yet in place) and therefore this function needs to first make sure
4889 there's no lingering previous data allocated. */
4890 Curl_free_request_state(data);
4891
4892 memset(&data->req, 0, sizeof(struct SingleRequest));
4893 data->req.maxdownload = -1;
4894
4895 conn->socktype = SOCK_STREAM; /* most of them are TCP streams */
4896
4897 /* Perform setup complement if some. */
4898 p = conn->handler;
4899
4900 if(p->setup_connection) {
4901 result = (*p->setup_connection)(conn);
4902
4903 if(result)
4904 return result;
4905
4906 p = conn->handler; /* May have changed. */
4907 }
4908
4909 if(conn->port < 0)
4910 /* we check for -1 here since if proxy was detected already, this
4911 was very likely already set to the proxy port */
4912 conn->port = p->defport;
4913
4914 return CURLE_OK;
4915}

4917/*
4918 * Curl_free_request_state() should free temp data that was allocated in the
4919 * Curl_easy for this single request.
4920 */
4921
4922void Curl_free_request_state(struct Curl_easy *data)
4923{
4924 Curl_safefree(data->req.protop);
4925 Curl_safefree(data->req.newurl);
4926}
